</taxonomicName>
is a common and widespread species in the savanna zones of trop­
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03421E604C4EFFB9FED9F8C86A5AF8F8" blockId="40.[264,1324,1354,1900]" box="[264,1322,1834,1860]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">ical Africa. It has totally infuscated brown wings with darker spots on crossveins and</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03421E604C4EFFB9FED9F8B06B5CF8D0" blockId="40.[264,1324,1354,1900]" box="[264,1068,1874,1900]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
brown vestiture. It can only be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="C4FD65E34C4EFFB9FCF3F8B06CFCF8D7" box="[802,908,1874,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Ligyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
